Perhaps this way of doing things made sense while learning the basics, but now with inheritance you have to up your game.

The first thing you have to do is to turn these methods into *instance* methods instead of static.  This is done by removing the `static` keyword. Then, in order to invoke those methods, you are going to need instances.  So, you cannot be invoking `NakedSingle.getHint(...)` anymore, you are going to have to do `NakedSingle nakedSingle = new NakedSingle();` and then `nakedSingle.getHint(...)`. 

